<h2 id="project-overview"><span class="prefix"></span><span class="content"><strong>Project Overview</strong></span><span class="suffix"></span></h2>
<p>This dataset titled <strong>“Watching Data”</strong> is collected to analyze and <strong>predict the time students spend watching videos based on multiple variables.</strong> The data is particularly suitable for simple and multiple linear regression analysis to understand the relationship between various factors (such as students’ cognitive load, course content difficulty, and viewing environment) and video viewing time. In addition, this dataset can also be used in the field of <strong>Learning Analytics</strong> to help educators and researchers better understand students’ learning behaviors and interaction patterns. In this project, by analyzing students’ video viewing behavior, we can deeply explore which factors affect students’ concentration and viewing time. Using the tools and methods of learning analytics, educators can <strong>develop personalized learning paths based on this data to improve students’ learning outcomes.</strong> In addition, this dataset can also be analyzed through machine learning models to predict students’ possible participation patterns and learning outcomes, providing data support for the optimization of learning platforms and teaching content.</p>

<h3 id="dataset-structure"><span class="prefix"></span><span class="content"><strong>Dataset Structure</strong>:</span><span class="suffix"></span></h3>
<p>The dataset is provided in a CSV format and contains the following columns:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Year</strong>: The year when the data was collected.</li>
<li><strong>Group</strong>: Student group identifier (e.g., ‘B’).</li>
<li><strong>Watched</strong>: Whether the video was watched or not (binary, 1 = watched, 0 = not watched).</li>
<li><strong>Watching Time</strong>: The total time (in minutes) the student spent watching the video.</li>
<li><strong>Score 1</strong>: The first score recorded for the student.</li>
<li><strong>Score 2</strong>: The second score recorded for the student.</li>
</ol>
<p>The primary objective of this dataset is to use <strong>linear regression models</strong> to predict the <em>Watching Time</em> based on other variables such as whether the video was watched, the group identifier, and the scores (Score 1 and Score 2).</p>
